The Director General of Buhari Campaign Organisation and Minister for Transport, Rotimi Amaechi, has said the All Progressives Congress (APC) has delivered on its promises to Nigerians. Speaking during the flag-off of the South-South campaigns for President Muhammadu Buhari in Uyo, Akwa Ibom state, Amaechi said the party have fulfilled its promise to improve the economy, ensure security and fight corruption. He noted that the party promised to bring about change in the country and it had achieved that, adding that changes donâ€™t come easily. He denied that the party promised to make the Naira equivalent to the dollar and to bring down the price of petrol, adding that the party has created employment for Nigerians. He said even the opposition have testified to the fact that President Buhari was fighting corruption, saying he is not corrupt.